\centerline{\bbf Domain Names vs. Internet Numbers}

%(Comer: Chapter 20)

Humans: names \qquad Machines: numbers

Host name: like a address,
\break
Internet number: like a zip code + 4

Post Office:
\break
Addresses are used by humans,
\break
mail is delivered using zip code.

Internet:
\break
Host names are used by humans,
\break
messages are delivered using internet numbers.
\break
Internet numbers have 32-bits (4-octets).

Principle: numbers reflect wires (cables/fiber)
\break
Principle: names reflect organization
\break
$\Rightarrow$ mapping may be complicated

Delivery principle: zip codes uniquely specify the destination

To avoid duplication zip codes are assigned.

Principle: To avoid duplication internet numbers and host names
must be centrally assigned.
