\centerline{\bbf Delegation}

With millions machines on the internet;
\break
Centrally managing that many names and numbers is impossible.

Solution: delegate, issue names and numbers in blocks.
\break
Such a block is called an {\bit internet license}.
\break
Let the local authorities handle individual machines. 

The Long Beach license:
\break
All internet names ending in {\ltt{}csulb.edu}
\break
All internet numbers starting with {\ltt{}134.139}

Our internet names: must end in {\ltt{}csulb.edu},
\break
but we choose any prefixes we want.
\break
Internet numbers: must start with {\ltt{}134.139},
\break
but we choose any postfixes

\halign{#\quad\hfil&#\hfil\cr
{\ltt{}cheetah.cecs.csulb.edu}&{\ltt{}134.139.248.2}\cr
{\ltt{}elmo.acs.csulb.edu}&{\ltt{}134.139.60.7}\cr
{\ltt{}mercator.geog.csulb.edu}&{\ltt{}134.139.60.51}\cr}

We choose names to reflect campus political organization.

We choose numbers to reflect physical location on the campus network.
